The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index fell 2.1 percent to 39,214.64, the biggest
drop since Nov. 25.  America Movil SAB (AMXL)  , the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , tumbled 8.2 percent to
17.13 pesos. The company is offering 2.6 billion euros ($3.4
billion) to boost its stake in Dutch phone company Royal KPN NV
to as high as 28 percent.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), a Mexican miner of
silver and gold, fell 0.8 percent to 608.76 pesos. Gold and
silver futures tumbled amid concern austerity efforts in  Greece 
may be derailed.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , Mexicoâ€™s biggest mining
company, fell 0.9 percent to 40.98 pesos. Copper futures
retreated as European concerns dimmed the outlook for demand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
